5:
Hey, guys? I've got some big news. 
I got the green light from 3MM to
keep the Shibuya branch open.
9:
Oh, seriously? I thought we were
only open for the winter.
13:
Well, with all the monsters coming
from underground, it's safe to
assume Shibuya's got a connection
to the Kaleidoscope.
15:
And with Magia Fest coming up, the
locals will have their hands full with
prep and what not. That's where we
come in.
19:
There's a lot of innocent children
who call this place home, and we're
going to make sure it stays that way.
22:
Ahh. She DEFINITELY had a talk with
Mr. Takamori...
25:
Does that mean you're transferring
over to this branch for good?
31:
Well, that's the pickle... I'm still kinda
stumped on what to do.
34:
If I'm being real with myself, it's not
the idea of quitting 3MM that's
holding me back.
39: Really? I thought you loved your job.
43:
I do, but... What's really bugging me
is the idea of forcing my whole team
to go freelance like me.
46:
I don't wanna get the team wrapped
up in my mess, y'know?
49:
But... I'm their chief. It'd be a real pain
for all of them if I just up and left.
52:
Asking them to transfer to another
department is one thing. But
transferring to a whole new WORLD?
Yeesh.
55:
Yeah... Sounds like a difficult
adjustment.
58:
If you're worried about them, why
don't you just transfer by yourself?
64:
Ding-ding-ding! That would be the
most logical answer. But somehow,
that one makes me feel the worst of
all...
68:
In the end, no matter what world 
I end up in... I'd be lost without my
team.
73: Ah, I see. So that's how it is.
79:
Yup. That's exactly how it is! I know
it's selfish of me, but... 
I just CAN'T do this without them!
84:
Then why don't you talk to them?
You're not gonna get anywhere
freaking out by yourself.
89:
Sho, you might want to consider
taking your own advice once in a
while.
93:
But, he's right... I need to get myself
together.
97: All right! I'll talk to the team!
102:
So... there you have it! Now, who
wants to make the jump to Shibuya
with me?!
105:
Got it. I'll make arrangements to
move from tomorrow.
107:
You don't need to decide right away
or anything, so—
112:
Wait, WHAT?! You mean you're in?
Already?!
115:
Of course we are. You didn't really
think we'd let you go all by yourself
now, did you?
119:
Well, uh... No. But I thought it would
take a little more convincing...
122: Oho... You know us all too well, Chief.
125:
But seriously, have you thought this
through? I mean, you've gotta
move! And we're not talking down
the street—it's another WORLD!
128:
Oh, since I saw how well you were
getting along in Shibuya, I've been
preparing myself for this day.
130:
Plenty of drinkin' buddies around
those parts. No complaints from me.
132:
Just follow your heart, missy.
Wherever you go, we go.
135:
Wow... Really? This feels almost too
good to be true.
138:
Let me guess... You're wondering
how everything worked out so well in
the end?
142:
Right! Exactly! But I mean, I'm SUPER
thankful.
145:
But isn't this great? Now there's
nothing else holding you back!
149: Nyahaha! you've got that right, Alk!
152:
I never do things halfway. And
neither does my team!
157:
So that settles it! From here on out,
the Special Equipment Defense
Force's Shibuya team is takin' the
underground by storm!
163: This is gonna be a BLAAAAAST!
166:
Heya, old man! How's B-Squad
holding up?
168:
Business is a-boomin'! Literally! You
certainly picked the right
commanding officer for the job.
170:
Isn't she great? She's dealt with the
Kaleidoscope before, but she works
herself too hard...
174:
Nice work, Katyusha! That was some
fancy footwork out there.
178:
I can't take the credit. That was all
my team. Really, they probably don't
even need me.
181:
Nuh-uh-uh! You need to believe in
yourself. Thanks to you, B-Squad's
target neutralization efficiency has
skyrocketed.
184:
But don't burn yourself out! If you
ever need a day off or something,
just say the word!
We all need breaks—me, Cocoa,
and Mocha are heading to Qualia
City tomorrow!
188: That means a lot, boss... Thank you.
192:
Great. Juuust great... Now I'll have to
fudge the reports even more...
196:
Hey, Carbina. You sound kinda
miffed. Are you upset because we
resigned from the other branch of
the team?
200:
Quite the opposite, actually. The
department was starting to feel a
little too cramped with all of you
there.
205:
Nyaha! You're such a straight
shooter! I love that about you.
210:
Besides, you seem content. And
your requirement numbers are
nothing to scoff at either. You might
just be CEO material, Tink.
215:
Nah, I'm not cut out to be the big
boss. Being chief is juuust right for
me.
218:
But here's an idea! If the monster
problem ends up spreading to
another world, we can always just
start a new branch!
222:
I would be in a world of hurt with the
company if I ever did something like
that.
227:
Nyahaha! Then why don't you just
join us in Shibuya? We've got plenty
of room!
232:
That would be an honor, but I'll have
to pass. I actually feel like I'm
well-suited to my present position.
235:
Look alive, dearies! The infested
building has been cleared of all
civilians. You're good to go.
236:
Alk and the gang are standin' by!
But don't you two rookies stick your
necks out too far now, you hear?
238:
Ahhh! Mocha, we're getting called
out! Good thing we've been
practicing—we gotta show 'em our
stuff this time.
240:
You got it. We may be the newbies,
but we'll pull our weight!
244:
Heck yeah! Let's blow the ROOF offa
this place!
